parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering assist fails
the steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the vehicle loses power steering functionality
the power steering fault message is displayed
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
and the vehicle becomes difficult to maneuver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or speed
the check engine or wrench light illuminates
the accelerator pedal feels unresponsive
the vehicle surges or hesitates
the engine RPMs increase or decrease without adjusting the accelerator pedal
the vehicle goes into "limp" mode.
